PN,46806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1776280294
OL,3,C3,000 jobs promised as nuclear power
OL,4,Cstation works begin
OL,6,FThat closure was extended but in 2015
OL,7,FWylfa's last reactor was closed down,
OL,8,Fbeginning the decommissioning process
OL,9,Fand ending 44 years of operations at
OL,10,Fthe site.
OL,12,FAt the time of its closure, it was
OL,13,FBritain's oldest nuclear power station.
OL,15,FPlans by Japanese-owned company
OL,16,FHorizon Nuclear Power in 2009 to build
OL,17,Ftwo advanced boiling water reactors on
OL,18,Fthe site were eventually shelved in
OL,19,F2019.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,469,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1776280294
OL,3,C3,000 jobs promised as nuclear power
OL,4,Cstation works begin
OL,6,FHorizon's chief executive, Duncan
OL,7,FHawthorne, stated at the time that
OL,8,F"despite the best efforts of everyone
OL,9,Finvolved," they had been unable "to
OL,10,Freach an agreement to the satisfaction
OL,11,Fof all concerned."
OL,13,FHe added that Horizon would "keep the
OL,14,Foption to resume development in
OL,15,Ffuture."
OL,17,FIn 2021, then Prime Minister Boris
OL,18,FJohnson said the UK government was
OL,19,Factively looking at proposals for a
OL,20,Fnew nuclear power plant at Wylfa.
OL,26,@qD@JO]qD@aOUuD@]OU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/8
